					<description><![CDATA[I changed my environment to get up without snoozing, by switching from my traditional alarm clock to a new alarm from my cell phone. (I was going to buy a new alarm clock, but then realized my phone could do that job).

I practiced my new ritual of throwing off the covers and sitting up BEFORE turning off my new alarm... I did it about 3 times. Yes, I practiced getting up. I did this to create the routine in my brain. Then from day 1, I didn&#039;t have to think... my brain just played the new routine in response to the new alarm (and from a new alarm source). Three weeks later, it&#039;s still working.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I changed my environment to get up without snoozing, by switching from my traditional alarm clock to a new alarm from my cell phone. (I was going to buy a new alarm clock, but then realized my phone could do that job).</p>
<p>I practiced my new ritual of throwing off the covers and sitting up BEFORE turning off my new alarm&#8230; I did it about 3 times. Yes, I practiced getting up. I did this to create the routine in my brain. Then from day 1, I didn&#8217;t have to think&#8230; my brain just played the new routine in response to the new alarm (and from a new alarm source). Three weeks later, it&#8217;s still working.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
